korean:
  title: 소우
  author: 서거정
  language: kor
  text: |-
    아침에 오는 가랑비가 더욱 보슬거리어
    지는 버들개지와 날으는 꽃이 온 밭에 가득 찬다
    90일의 봄도 이제 이미 저무는데
    앓은 뒤의 술잔을 힘없이 거푸 잡는다
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1450_020_0070&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Light Rain
  author: Seo Geo-jeong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Morning brings the finest drizzle,
    More delicate than silk threads.
    Falling catkins and drifting blossoms
    Fill the entire window frame.

    Ninety days of spring have already faded—
    The season closes in upon itself.
    Sick and weary, I reach for the wine cup again,
    With trembling, listless hands.
  footnotes:
    - The 'ninety days of spring' refers to the traditional three months of spring, a classical allusion marking the passage of time and the transience of the season.
    - The falling catkins and blossoms represent spring's ephemeral beauty, a common metaphor in East Asian poetry for the fleeting nature of life and youth.
